ion":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Bowyer was born about 1385, in Knypersley, Staffordshire, England, his father, William Bowyer, was 19 and his mother, Margaret Trubshawe, was 19. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth Erdeswick. He died in 1429, in England, at the age of 45."},"et":{"about 1385–1429":"umbes 1385–1429","1385–1429":"1385–1429","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1367–1429":"1367–1429","1367–1466":"1367–1466","1466":"1466","1367":"1367","1454":"1454","1410":"1410","before 1397":"enne 1397","1385":"1385","about 1410":"umbes 1410","about 1385":"umbes 1385","1429":"1429","1390":"1390","Knypersley, Staffordshire, England":"Knypersley, Staffordshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1385–1429":"noin 1385–1429","1385–1429":"1385–1429","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1367–1429":"1367–1429","1367–1466":"1367–1466","1466":"1466","1367":"1367","1454":"1454","1410":"1410","before 1397":"ennen vuotta 1397","1385":"1385","about 1410":"noin 1410","about 1385":"noin 1385","1429":"1429","1390":"1390","Knypersley, Staffordshire, England":"Knypersley, Staffordshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1385–1429":"environ 1385–1429","1385–1429":"1385–1429","1390–Female":"1390–Décédée","1410–1454":"1410–1454